<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,236,954]" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">
Diagnosis. The new species can be distinguished from its congeners by possessing the following combination of characteristics: small body size, SL mean 
<quantity box="[592,663,513,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="50.0">50 mm</quantity>
in males and 
<quantity box="[817,888,514,538]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" unit="mm" value="60.0">60 mm</quantity>
in females; a small jet spot far smaller than the eye diameter on the upper part of the caudal peduncle; 7–8 narrow rows of dark spots on the caudal fin (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1290,548,573]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Figs 8–9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1300,1371,549,573]" captionStart="Figures 14–17" captionStartId="8.[155,227,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,562,1989]" captionTargetId="figure-180@8.[189,1398,562,1989]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 14–17. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., color in life. 14, 16. Lateral view. 15, 17. Dorsal view. Scale bars =1cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617696" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617696/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">14–17</figureCitation>
); males with a slender and finely serrated lamina circularis at the base of the first branched pectoral fin ray (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1295,583,607]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); mental lobes undeveloped, two superficial longitudinal lobes short and bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[964,1046,618,642]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); suborbital spine straight, with long processus medio-caudalis (
<figureCitation box="[428,510,652,676]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen YX &amp; Chen YF" authorityName="Chen YX &amp; Chen YF" authorityYear="2018" box="[531,995,652,676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Cobitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[531,747,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Cobitis brachysoma</emphasis>
Chen YX &amp; Chen YF
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1007,1095,652,676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1007,1095,652,676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Chen. These" authorityYear="2011" box="[1242,1422,652,676]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cobitidae" genus="Cobitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="microcephala">
<emphasis box="[1242,1422,652,676]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">C. microcephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in body size and shape of lamina circularis, but differs from it in having long processus medio-caudalis of suborbital spine (vs. short); caudal peduncle short, length of caudal peduncle 7.3–9.2 (mean 8.4) in SL in males and 7.0–9.9 (mean 8.5) in females (vs. caudal peduncle long, length of caudal peduncle 5.9–6.6 (mean 6.3) in SL in males and 5.3–7.2 (mean 6.3) in females); body slender, depth 6.1–6.6 (mean 6.4) in SL in males and 5.5–8.6 (mean 6.8) in females (vs. sturdy, depth 5.8–6.2 (mean 5.9) in SL in males and 5.0–6.5 (mean 5.6) in females).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,236,954]" lastBlockId="8.[136,1452,236,503]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="164" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">
Description (
<figureCitation box="[330,441,860,884]" captionStart-0="Figures 8–13" captionStart-1="Figures 14–17" captionStartId-0="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionStartId-1="8.[155,227,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox-0="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetBox-1="[189,1398,562,1989]" captionTargetId-0="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId-1="figure-180@8.[189,1398,562,1989]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." captionText-1="Figures 14–17. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., color in life. 14, 16. Lateral view. 15, 17. Dorsal view. Scale bars =1cm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617696" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4617696/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163">Figs 8–17</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[454,539,860,884]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="6.[136,192,950,971]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Table 2. Morphometric and meristic characters for the two new species of Cobitis, all measurements given in millimeters (mm)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5FE7DFAFFFAEE51DCBFFDBE7FA2CE9B1" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" tableUuid="5FE7DFAFFFAEE51DCBFFDBE7FA2CE9B1">Table 2</tableCitation>
). D. III–7; A. III–5; 
<collectionCode box="[766,788,861,884]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
. I–6; P. I–7–8; C. IV–14–16–IV. Body small, elongated, and compressed. Head small and compressed. Snout rounded. Eyes located on upper part and middle of head. Preorbital part of head shorter than postorbital part of head. Mouth small, inferior, with three pairs of short barbels. Length of maxillomandibular barbels longer than diameter of eye. Mental lobes undeveloped, two superficial longitudinal lobes short and bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[327,409,271,295]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="164">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Suborbital spine bifid, relatively slender and straight, with a long processus medio-caudalis. Processus latero-caudalis short, less than one-fifth of processus medio-caudalis (
<figureCitation box="[1002,1082,306,330]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="164">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Subdorsal scales small and oval, with a larger focal area, 17–21 radial grooves, and 4–8 supplementary ones (
<figureCitation box="[953,1031,340,364]" captionStart="Figures 8–13" captionStartId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-484@7.[189,1398,986,1930]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 8–13. Cobitis brachysoma Chen YX &amp; Chen YF, sp. nov., Suijiang River, Guangning, Guangdong, China. 8. Holotype, HU 1506334, lateral view. 9. HU 1506307, lateral view. 10. Lamina circularis in the pectoral in of male, dorsal view. 11. Mouth characters, front view. 12. Suborbital spine, left dorsal view, right interior view. 13. Subdorsal scales, dorsal view. Scale bars: 8–9= 1cm; 10–12 =1mm; 13=100μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="164">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4617694" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4617694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4617694/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="163" startId="7.[155,227,1967,1989]" targetBox="[189,1398,986,1930]" targetPageId="7">
